      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need some help with a professional email. I'm an HR manager at a logistics company and I have to write a formal reprimand to an employee. They've been about 15 minutes late to every shift for the last two weeks. I need it to be firm and professional but not like, unnecessarily aggressive. Can you draft something for me?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Urgent: Addressing Attendance Concerns\n\nDear [Employee's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I am writing to address a matter of significant concern regarding your attendance at work. Over the past two weeks, it has come to our attention that you have been arriving approximately 15 minutes late to each of your shifts. While we understand that unforeseen circumstances can occasionally cause delays, consistent tardiness is impacting team morale and operational efficiency.\n\nIn the spirit of maintaining a harmonious work environment and ensuring that we all contribute to our shared goals, we must address this issue promptly. We value your contributions and believe that with a little more punctuality, you can continue to be an integral part of our team.\n\nPlease understand that this is not a matter to be taken lightly. We are committed to supporting you in any way we can to help you get back on track. If you are facing personal challenges that are affecting your punctuality, we are here to listen and offer assistance.\n\nMoving forward, we kindly ask that you make every effort to arrive on time for your shifts. We appreciate your cooperation and understanding in this matter.\n\nThank you for your attention to this important issue.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company",
